Reasoning: The paper deals with the mathematical representation and analysis of functional shapes, which are relevant in fields such as medical imaging and computational anatomy. The concept of functional currents is introduced as a new mathematical framework to model and process these shapes. Given this focus, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with image and signal processing. The paper also involves geometric and functional analysis, which suggests the sub-categories cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely candidates. The use of a Hilbertian norm and processing algorithms points towards cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the registration of functional shapes under diffeomorphic transport suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a potential sub-category.
